post_text: Today (Friday, May 22nd) was the final day of Grab N' Go meal service at our ALA Anthem and San Tan Valley campuses. Beginning Tuesday, May 26th, Grab N' Go meals will only be available at our ALA Ironwood High School campus (located at 850 W. Combs Road Queen Creek, AZ 85140). We encourage families to take advantage of this meal program extension offered at ALA Ironwood High School this summer!

post_text: Congratulations Senior Patriots! Twelve seniors at American Leadership Academy Queen Creek High School were awarded the 2020 State Seal of Fine Arts Proficiency during the inaugural year of the new program implemented by the Arizona Department of Education. ALA was one of 58 high schools in Arizona to participate in this program.
shared_text:
ALASCHOOLS.ORG
ALA Seniors Graduate with State Seal of Arts Proficiency

American Leadership Academy - Queen Creek Jr. High-High School
May 11 at 1:56 PM ·

Senior Shout Out!! Congrats to the following seniors who will graduate with the State Seal of Arts Proficiency in the following categories. This was the inaugural year for the program by the Arizona Department of Education.

Dance Seals
-Keli Ann Shinsato
-William Whitlock
-Andra Graham

Media Arts Seal
-Kadence Lawlor

Music Seal
-Reagan Metz

Theatre Arts Seals
-Aisha Brown
-Justin Palmer
-Kara Randall
-Ashton Spencer
-Christian Bribiescas
-Finn Hesler
-Phoebe Chandler

post_text: Mrs. Edges from ALA Gilbert North High School introduces us to a fun but challenging engineering project using gummy worms and paper clips! Check it out!
text: Mrs. Edges from ALA Gilbert North High School introduces us to a fun but challenging engineering project using gummy worms and paper clips! Check it out!

post_text:
👋🏻 Hey there! Today on Facebook LIVE with ALA, Gilbert North 8th-grade science and robotics teacher, Mrs. Edges, will be leading a fun project called Save Fred! Log onto American Leadership Academy Schools at 12:30 to join the fun!

Save Fred is a family-friendly and fun engineering challenge. The goal of Save Fred is to save him from drowning! Materials needed are:
-gummy life savers
-gummy worms
-a plastic cup
-4 paper clips

Groups work in teams of 2 to only use the 4 paperclips to get the gummy life saver on Fred without him falling off the bottom of the plastic cup. You can't use your hands or anything else - just the paper clips. Family teams can compete against each other for the fastest Save Fred time. Super fun, super collaborative, hope to see you there~.

post_text: We are cooking a delicious crispy rice treat called scotcheroos. Here is what you will need: 1 cup sugar, 1 cup corn syrup, 1 cup peanut butter, 6 cups rice krispy cereal, 1 bag chocolate chips, 1 bag butterscotch chips. You will also need a stove and a pot to heat the ingredients, a bowl and spoon for mixing, and a flat baking pan for shaping (I use a cookie sheet). Let's get cooking!

post_text: What a great story!! Way to go, Ruby!!
shared_text:
GILBERTSUNNEWS.COM
At 13, Gilbert girl a commercial baker

American Leadership Academy - Gilbert North Jr. High - High School
April 13 at 2:23 PM ·

Our very own Ruby Williams was featured in the Gilbert Sun News last week! At only 13, she opened Ruby’s Rockin’ Sweet Shop last year selling her baked goods at various local markets.

Ruby’s menu offerings include coconut macaroons, twisted caramel chocolate pretzel rods, tarts, mini cookie pies, doughnuts, coffee cake and much more. 😋

If you would like to support Ruby, she is accepting orders online and pickups are made at the SwimHaus in Gilbert each Saturday between 10-11 AM! https://shopmadewithlovemarket.com/collections/rubys-rockin-sweet-shop

We are proud of you Ruby! ❤️ 🍰

post_text:
ALA performing arts students competed in an optional ALA district essay contest while we have been away from campus. Out of about 30 essays submitted, here are our winners, congratulations!!

The winners were chosen by a Broadway performer whose credits include: ”Les Miserables", "Mary Poppins", “Wicked" and "Phantom of the Opera".

Here were the four prompts students could choose from:
•Why are the Fine Arts important in our schools?
• How has performing helped you in areas of peer leadership?
• How has sharing your talents helped you serve others?
• How do the Performing arts strengthen you emotionally?

Grab N' Go Meals UPDATE! ALA will provide breakfast and lunch at our Anthem, San Tan Valley, and Ironwood High School campuses throughout the duration of the state-mandated school closure. Both breakfast and lunch meals will be dispersed to families at the same time, so each family may choose to receive both a breakfast meal and a lunch meal for every child between the ages of 0-18 at these locations. We will serve each day, rain or shine!

If your family is not in close proximity to our Anthem, San Tan, or Ironwood campuses where we have established the grab-and-go meals, we encourage you to check out additional locations where your children
can be provided free meals during the state-mandated school closure.
Many District schools (Mesa, Gilbert, Chandler, J.O. Combs, Florence, Queen Creek and Higley) have set up sites that may be convenient for your family. Please check their website postings for the most updated information regarding locations and times. We love you ALA nation! ❤️

post_text:
Mrs. Barden and her family from ALA Anthem showed us a great example of integrity yesterday! She is the ALA district winner for integrity #RAISEofSunshine! Here is what she told us:

"I was hiking up “F” Mountain and when we got back to our car this was on our windshield. We hadn’t lost any AirPods but it was a great opportunity to have a conversation with my kids about integrity. When you find something that isn’t yours, you should always do your best to find the rightful owners. We talked about how we would feel if we lost something that was important to us and how we would feel to find something that is important to somebody else and be able to return it. To us, integrity is doing what is right, even if no one is looking." 👏🏻 👏🏻

We talked about how we would feel if we lost something that was important to us and how we would feel to find something that is important to somebody else and be able to return it. To us, integrity is doing what is right, even if no one is looking." 👏🏻 👏🏻

On February 1st, the 2019 – 2020 American Leadership Academy Gilbert North Junior High Boy’s Varsity Basketball team completed an undefeated season winning the Canyon Athletic Association’s state championship for Junior High boy’s basketball. The ALA Eagles Junior High Varsity finished their CAA season with a record of 19 – 0. Check out more impressive stats and accomplishments for boys basketball on our athletics website: https://alagnathletics.com/2020/02/10/junior-high-boys-basketball-dominate-the-2019-2020-caa-season/

post_text: Congratulations to our Patriots who signed their letters of intent yesterday!!
shared_text:
American Leadership Academy - Queen Creek Jr. High-High School
February 6 at 12:47 PM ·

🎉 🏈 ⚽ Congratulations to our Seniors that signed their letters of intent yesterday to play college athletics! Your Patriot family couldn't be more proud of all your hard work put in at ALA. We are excited to see you continue to thrive at the college level!

Congratulations to the following Patriots:
-Dean Jones signed with BYU Football
-Rand Jensen signed with Southern Utah Football
-Taylor Atkin signed with NAU Football
-Ethen Cluff signed with NAU Football
-Zach Robertson signed with Snow College Athletics Football Team
-Jessie Watson signed with Chandler-Gilbert Community College's Women's Soccer Team

Thank you to Coach Rich Edwards and all of our Patriot coaches who helped to get our students to where they are today! Also, special shout out to former NFL and BYU quarterback Ty Detmer, ALA's Executive Director of District Athletics, and Buddy Allen, ALA's District Athletic Director of Operations, for their continued support of our excelling athletic programs. Go Patriots!
